Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.64,0:11:19.49,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Misaki! Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.49,0:11:20.20,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.20,0:11:21.15,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.45,0:11:23.45,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,In the back yard.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.45,0:11:24.46,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Are you hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.46,0:11:26.40,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.40,0:11:28.75,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I can't move, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.56,0:11:31.21,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,I'm on my way. Just—
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.21,0:11:32.44,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.11,0:11:34.14,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.66,0:11:38.00,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,You don't want to \Ncome here, Sakakibara.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.00,0:11:39.21,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.98,0:11:40.72,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.34,0:11:44.16,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I have to stop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.74,0:11:49.73,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,No way... Misaki, who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.27,0:11:52.00,Default,Misaki,0,0,0,,You'll regret coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.56,0:11:53.67,Default,Misaki,0,0,0,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.24,0:12:04.45,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Misaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.39,0:12:08.56,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Misaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.20,0:12:11.91,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Stay back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.94,0:12:17.92,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,We have to help!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.92,0:12:18.84,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,We can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.32,0:12:24.34,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I... I can see the color of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.09,0:12:28.97,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Did... you figure it out just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.69,0:12:35.10,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I've known it for a while, \Nbut I couldn't tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.54,0:12:36.40,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Still...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.01,0:12:41.36,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Still... I have to stop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.36,0:12:41.90,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.18,0:12:48.49,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.49,0:12:51.00,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,No way... No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.86,0:12:52.83,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.89,0:12:55.97,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,She's... the extra person?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.38,0:12:58.55,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.38,0:13:02.44,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Are you... really sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.20,0:13:05.43,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Ms. Mikami...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.26,0:13:08.87,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Reiko is the extra?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.32,0:13:10.50,Default,Reiko,0,0,0,,Kouichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.30,0:13:14.78,Default,Reiko,0,0,0,,{\i1}Now, the fourth thing you need to know to prepare yourself for Yomi North is...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.19,0:13:22.24,Default,Reiko,0,0,0,,{\i1}Keep my work and \Npersonal life separate.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.24,0:13:25.56,Default,Reiko,0,0,0,,{\i1}Try not to call me \NReiko mistakenly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.56,0:13:30.16,Default,Reiko,0,0,0,,{\i1}Remember that, during school,\NI'm Ms. Mikami—the assistant homeroom teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.16,0:13:30.95,Default,Reiko,0,0,0,,{\i1}All right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.64,0:13:35.91,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Is there another assistant \Nhomeroom teacher in our school?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.37,0:13:37.43,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.03,0:13:39.06,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,They don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.94,0:13:43.77,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Ninth grade's class 3 is the only one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.89,0:13:48.72,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,This year, our classroom had the correct number of desks,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.38,0:13:52.55,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,and yet the calamity \Nbegan in April.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.21,0:13:54.43,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Why do you think that is?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.26,0:13:58.56,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Because the room \Nthat was short one desk...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.16,0:14:01.86,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,...was the faculty room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.86,0:14:04.16,Default,Reiko,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.16,0:14:05.37,Default,Reiko,0,0,0,,That's not true!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.51,0:14:10.31,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Sakakibara. Step aside.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.84,0:14:32.76,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,I'll... I'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.62,0:14:38.64,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,I'll send the dead back to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.29,0:14:41.56,Default,Reiko,0,0,0,,Kouichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.93,0:14:44.43,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Reiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.16,0:14:48.22,Default,Reiko,0,0,0,,Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.22,0:14:49.67,Default,Reiko,0,0,0,,Don't do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.05,0:14:52.19,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,{\i1}Is this okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.19,0:14:53.41,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,{\i1}Is this really okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.87,0:14:55.41,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,{\i1}Is this the right choice?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.94,0:14:57.41,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,{\i1}No mistaking it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.82,0:15:01.17,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,{\i1}If we're wrong, then \NI'll have murdered Reiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.83,0:15:04.90,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,{\i1}Is Misaki telling the truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.90,0:15:06.28,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,{\i1}Can I trust her?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.85,0:15:10.51,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I remembered that I saw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.72,0:15:12.99,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I was watching.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.28,0:15:56.95,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I saw Ms. Mikami being \Nmurdered a year and a half ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.76,0:16:00.23,Default,Bird,0,0,0,,{\i1}Cheer! Cheer up!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.23,0:16:03.60,Default,Bird,0,0,0,,{\i1}Why? Why, Rei?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.62,0:16:03.60,Sign,Text,0,0,0,,{\an5\fnKinesis Std\b0\c&H262828&\blur0.7\fs24\fax-0.05\pos(794,345)\frz17.56}Certificate \Nof Excellence \NPresented to \NReiko Mikami
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.99,0:16:06.48,Default,Tamie,0,0,0,,{\i1}It was about a year and a half ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.15,0:16:08.98,Default,Tamie,0,0,0,,{\i1}It was at the pet shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.68,0:16:12.24,Default,Yousuke,0,0,0,,{\i1}How does it feel to be back in \NYomiyama after a year and a half?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.86,0:16:14.50,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,{\i1}A year and a half ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.50,0:16:16.96,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,{\i1}I hit you with an empty can.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.96,0:16:17.99,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,{\i1}Do you remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.99,0:16:22.16,Sign,Ryouhei,0,0,0,,{\an8\blur0.5\fnBalzano\fs48\b1\i0\fscy90\3c&H29534A&\bord2\blur2\3a&H66&\1a&H66&\pos(960,314)\c&H29534A&}Mikami
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.99,0:16:22.16,Sign,Ryouhei,0,0,0,,{\an8\blur0.5\fnBalzano\fs48\b1\i0\fscy90\3c&H29534A&\bord0\blur0.7\1a&H44&\pos(960,314)\c&H010302&}Mikami
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.35,0:16:22.16,Default,Ryouhei,0,0,0,,{\i1}A funeral always \Nfollows one's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.16,0:16:26.92,Default,Ryouhei,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm so tired of \Nfunerals... So very tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.92,0:16:32.01,Default,Ryouhei,0,0,0,,{\i1}My poor Ritsuko and Reiko...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.09,0:16:37.47,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Trust me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.66,0:17:18.85,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Reiko...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.67,0:17:24.15,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Goodbye, Reiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.91,0:17:36.64,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Goodbye, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.07,0:17:44.83,Sign,Grave,0,0,0,,{\an8\c&H545559&\bord1\3a&H66&\4a&H77&\yshad-1\blur0.5\fnBalzano\fs48\fscy90\b1\i0\pos(645,578)\3c&H39434D&\4c&H3F3D3C&}Mikami\NFamily Grave
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.07,0:17:44.83,Sign,Grave,0,0,0,,{\an8\3c&H545559&\bord0\blur0.4\c&H181B18&\fnBalzano\fs48\fscy90\b1\i0\pos(645,578)}Mikami\NFamily Grave
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.95,0:17:54.28,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,You're here too?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.33,0:17:59.52,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,How are your lungs holding up?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.52,0:18:00.76,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Fine, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.76,0:18:03.35,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,I don't think I can participate \Nduring gym, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.35,0:18:05.10,Sign,Grave(R),0,0,0,,{\an5\fnBalzano\b1\fax0.25\fay0.08\frz341.871\pos(871,403)\c&H151109&\4c&H52525D&\xshad-2\yshad1\blur0.5\4a&H33&}Tombstone
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.35,0:18:05.10,Sign,Grave(R),0,0,0,,{\an7\fnBalzano\b1\fax0.25\fay0.1\frz341.871\c&H151109&\4c&H52525D&\xshad-2\yshad1\blur0.5\4a&H33&\bord1\3a&H77&\pos(624,464)\3c&H1B1E30&}29.10. Reiko\N27.7. Ritsuko
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.21,0:18:08.51,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,No one else remembers Ms. Mikami.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.01,0:18:11.56,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,We're the only ones?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.70,0:18:22.84,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,She was probably worried about you becoming the ninth victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.66,0:18:26.34,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,So eight people died?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.17,0:18:31.04,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,Technically, there were \Nten victims in August.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.41,0:18:33.70,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Who were the other two?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.70,0:18:35.29,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,The manager and his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.47,0:18:39.34,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,They were Takabayashi's \Nmaternal grandparents.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.94,0:18:45.31,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,I'm told they were emotionally \Nbroken since his death.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.53,0:18:50.54,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,Ms. Mikami died during fall, \Na year and a half ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.69,0:18:55.28,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,She was stabbed by an \Nunknown assailant near the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.54,0:18:58.64,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,I can't really remember, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.74,0:19:02.41,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,Apparently Ms. Mikami was \Nthe dead person this year?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.69,0:19:06.51,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,That means there \Nwere seven deaths
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.51,0:19:08.66,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,in the calamity two years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.66,0:19:11.79,Sign,Text,0,0,0,,{\an8\fnApple Garamond\c&H3D3C3A&\b0\fscx100\fs96\pos(489,402)\blur0.4}Homeroom: Reiko Mikami
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.66,0:19:11.79,Sign,Text,0,0,0,,{\an8\fscx100\fnJennifer's Hand Writing\b1\blur0.5\c&H1D1B19&\pos(1002,406)}October 29, \Nmurdered
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.66,0:19:11.79,Sign,Text,0,0,0,,{\an7\c&H3D3192&\1a&H15&\blur0.5\p1\fscx66.25\fscy91.25\pos(651,455)}m -200 -58 b -66 19 201 69 349 54 30 50 -80 -6 -204 -62{\p0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.66,0:19:11.79,Sign,Text,0,0,0,,{\an7\c&H3D3192&\blur0.5\1a&H15&\p1\fscx66.25\fscy95\pos(674,451)}m -250 61 b -62 4 159 16 254 -56 105 22 -80 -2 -244 58{\p0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.91,0:19:11.79,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Yes. There were seven "X" marks.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.02,0:19:17.52,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,I saw the name "Akazawa" \Non the file from that year.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.11,0:19:19.00,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Was that...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.00,0:19:21.76,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Yes, he was Akazawa's cousin,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.76,0:19:24.12,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,but they were raised \Nmore like siblings.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.86,0:19:27.63,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,Do you two want a ride?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.25,0:19:30.89,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,No, we'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.30,0:19:32.48,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,All right, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.48,0:19:34.84,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,Be careful going home.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.68,0:19:36.91,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.91,0:19:40.33,Default,Chibiki,0,0,0,,I guess the calamity \Nis over now, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.31,0:19:53.63,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,When did you figure out that Reiko— that Ms. Mikami was the extra?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.01,0:19:56.47,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I wonder...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.15,0:19:59.30,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Dunno.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.61,0:20:02.13,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Why didn't you say anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.92,0:20:05.17,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Nothing good \Nwould've come from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.34,0:20:08.57,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,There was no way \NI could tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.10,0:20:12.10,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Ms. Mikami was special \Nto you, wasn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.28,0:20:14.72,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Sorry. I mean, Reiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.83,0:20:22.46,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Want to go check out \Nthat amusement park?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.46,0:20:23.32,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.27,0:20:26.83,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,The Ferris wheel.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.24,0:20:29.89,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I don't ride those.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.89,0:20:30.83,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.63,0:20:39.54,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,I tried to call your cell from \Nthe hospital the other day,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.54,0:20:41.08,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,but I couldn't connect.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.77,0:20:43.07,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.91,0:20:46.30,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I threw it in the \Nriver after that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.76,0:20:47.82,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.82,0:20:49.49,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I hate those devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.10,0:20:52.53,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,We don't always need to \Nbe connected through them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.03,0:20:57.56,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,She's probably going to \Ngive me another one, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.51,0:21:00.67,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,If she does,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.67,0:21:02.03,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,mind if I call you sometimes?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.27,0:21:06.56,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.99,0:21:09.34,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.34,0:21:12.28,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Mochizuki gave these to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.16,0:21:15.31,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,You can see Reiko in them, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.83,0:21:16.54,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.52,0:21:19.72,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,No one else could.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.71,0:21:24.27,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Even Mochizuki didn't \Nrealize she was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.82,0:21:26.09,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.40,0:21:27.78,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,What about the color?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.78,0:21:30.26,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,What color is Reiko?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.63,0:21:36.06,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I can see the color of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.73,0:21:42.47,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,I wonder if we \Ntoo will forget this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.09,0:21:46.16,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,The trip, what's \Nhappened since April,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.18,0:21:50.34,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,and everything that had \Nto do with Mikami Reiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.91,0:21:54.12,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Everything...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.74,0:21:59.67,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,You don't want to forget?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.62,0:22:02.00,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,You want to remember it forever?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.25,0:22:31.66,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,It's all over, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.17,0:22:59.89,ED-rom,,0,0,0,,{\blur3\fad(150,250)}iroaseteku firumu no you ni
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.17,0:22:59.89,ED-eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3\fad(150,250)}Just as the colors fade from old film
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.02,0:23:17.66,ED-rom,,0,0,0,,{\blur3\fad(150,250)}tashika na ima mo izure kasunde
